The paper focuses on network latency in mobile software, which suggests a focus on networking and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of prefetching and caching techniques, which are common in software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also touches on the issue of untrustworthy HTTP header information, which could fall under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper's focus on improving user experience suggests a potential connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
